import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
import time
# https://gist.github.com/greydanus/f6eee59eaf1d90fcb3b534a25362cea4
# https://stackoverflow.com/a/14434334
# this function is used to update the plots for each epoch and error
def plt_dynamic(x, vy, ty, ax, colors=['b']):
    ax.plot(x, vy, 'b', label="Validation Loss")
    ax.plot(x, ty, 'r', label="Train Loss")
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid()
    fig.canvas.draw()

In [18]:
from keras.optimizers import Adam,RMSprop,SGD
from keras.initializers import he_normal
def best_hyperparameters(activ,no_of_hidden_layers1,no_of_hidden_layers2,drop_out):
    output_dim=10
    input_dim=X_train.shape[1]
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(Dense(no_of_hidden_layers1, activation=activ, input_shape=(input_dim,), kernel_initializer=he_normal(seed=None)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(drop_out))
    model.add(Dense(no_of_hidden_layers2, activation=activ, kernel_initializer=he_normal(seed=None)))
    model.add(BatchNormalization())
    model.add(Dropout(drop_out))
    model.add(Dense(output_dim, activation='softmax'))
    model.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'], optimizer='adam')
    return model

activ = ['sigmoid','relu']
no_of_hidden_layers1=[50,350]
no_of_hidden_layers2=[40,150]
drop_out=[0.4,0.5]
from keras.wrappers.scikit_learn import KerasClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
model = KerasClassifier(build_fn=best_hyperparameters, epochs=5, verbose=0)
param_grid = dict(activ=activ,no_of_hidden_layers1=no_of_hidden_layers1,no_of_hidden_layers2=no_of_hidden_layers2,drop_out=drop_out)
grid = GridSearchCV(estimator=model, param_grid=param_grid)
grid_result = grid.fit(X_train, Y_train)

Results:¶

1. Tried Hyperparameter search on dropout and hidden layer 1 and hidden layer 2 and activations with only 5 epochs and found the best network to be 785-350-150-10 gives accuracy 0f 97.05% accuracy with sigmoid as cativation function with drop out rate equal to 0.4.¶

2. Since each parameter has 2 values the explored combinations are 16 slightly time consuming probably would have checked for more epochs to realize the full potential of relu function..¶
